Title: UPenn Visual Perception and Memory Study (Please accept the HIT before beginning the experiment)
Description: This website contains a series of tests designed to assess your perception ability and memory for faces and colors. These tests are part of a research study at the University of Pennsylvania, conducted by the Aguirre Lab.
Keywords: memory, vision, UPenn, study, perception, experiment, face, color, test, task,
Answer.feedback1: the faces were kind of weird

Answer.feedback1: It was very interesting; it took me a little time to actually figure out how the experiment would work.
Answer.feedback2: It was very hard to match the faces, and matching the colors was sometimes difficult too.  With both tasks, looking at the block in the center got confusing because of the center block changing as the mouse moved
Answer.feedback3: maybe provide one practice session, for people like me who have an easier time actually doing something rather than reading about how to do it
